cards.backText: Heillä on kartta. Heidän ei tarvitse kysyä tietä.

cards.frontText: He has a high fever. He doesn’t neeed to go to work.
cards.backText: Hänellä on korkea kuume. Hänen ei tarvitse mennä töihin.

cards.frontText: You (plural) are (have) hungry. You (plural) need to eat now.
cards.backText: Teillä on nälkä. Teidän täytyy syödä nyt.

cards.frontText: You (plural) are in a hurry. You (plural) need to leave early.
cards.backText: Teillä on kiire. Teidän täytyy lähteä aikaisin.

cards.frontText: to manage, to have enough strength, to be willing (to do something)
I have the stamina to walk home.
He has enough energy to study for an hour.
I can't manage to eat it all.
to make tired, to feel tired (Partitive + ____)
I feel tired all the time.
A long day makes him tired.
small box, pack (packaged unit of some item)
(verb) to get to, to reach.  Genitive + ____: in/after a time
In an hour, an hour later.
to fuss, to make a fuss (unnecessary or excessive concern) (puhekieli)
I make a fuss when the coffee being too hot. (puhekieli)
cards.backText: Mä hössötän, kun kahvi on liian kuumaa.

cards.frontText: Mom fusses when (I) don't eat breakfast. (puhekieli)
cards.backText: Äiti hössöttää, kun en syö aamupalaa.

cards.frontText: Snow clearing, snow removal work (usually in plural)
I keep (preserve) old photos in the box.
She keeps (preserves) wine in the cellar.
to transport, to carry. To drive, to give a ride
I carry books in my backpack.
He drives his children to school.
The patient doesn't need to be transported.
In a fever (you) need a lot drinkable. (you need to drink a lot)
(noun) Wound, sore (injury, such as a cut, stab or tear). Ulcer
Hygiene (practices to keep things heathy and clean)
to be sick with, to have a disease (____ + Partitive)
I am sick with a runny nose.
He is sick with a headache.
Adults are sick with from one to five colds a year.
cards.backText: Aikuiset sairastavat yhdestä viiteen flunssaa vuodessa.

cards.frontText: to be transmitted, to be contagious (of a disease)
I blow my nose every morning.
During the flu, she blows her nose often.
cards.backText: Flunssan aikana hän niistää nenäänsä usein.

cards.frontText: I sneeze often in the spring.
He sneezes often when he is ill.
cards.backText: Hän aivastaa usein, kun hän on sairas.

cards.frontText: Someone blows their nose or sneezes nearby.
to be related to, to be associated with, to join (____ + mihin)
She doesn't understand how music is related to mathematics.
cards.backText: Hän ei ymmärrä, miten musiikki liittyy matematiikkaan.

cards.frontText: A cold can be associated with a sorethroat, runny nose, and fever.
cards.backText: Flunssa voi liittyä kurkkukipua, nuhaa ja kuumetta.

cards.frontText: I have a headache. I need to rest in my room.
cards.backText: Minulla on päänsärky. Minun täytyy levätä huoneessani.

cards.frontText: to ease, to relieve, to mitigate
I ease my cough with tea.
He eases his hunger with an apple.
to continue, to go on, to last
Cough and runny nose can last for weeks.
cards.backText: Yskä ja nuha voivat jatkua viikkoja.

cards.frontText: (adv) over (related to time), past (related to space)
The party is over. (party in plural form)
Diarrhoeal diseases normally go away (over/past) in a couple of days.
cards.backText: Ripulitaudit menevät normaalisti ohi parissa päivässä.

cards.frontText: to cause, to lead to, to result in
I cause a queue at the cashier.
Heartburn (burning sensation in chest due to stomach acid reflux)
Fatty and spicy foods can cause heartburn.
cards.backText: Rasvaiset ja tuliset ruoat voivat aiheuttaa närästystä.

cards.frontText: to defend successfully, to ward off or fend off an attack
I fend off the cold with a jacket.
He wards off a bad mood with music.
Medication (Set of medicines given or taken for a health condition)

cards.etymology: Mihin form of the stem along (muka-)

cards.frontText: He is bleeding from his finger.
(You) can also put onto the neck a cold freezer bag.
cards.backText: Voit myös laittaa niskaan kylmän pakastepussin.

cards.frontText: I'm queuing for the doctor because I have an appointment at ten.
cards.backText: Minä jonotan lääkärille, koska minulla on aika kymmeneltä.

cards.frontText: She queues for the ice-cream stand by the river's bank.
Sometimes (one/you) have to queue, but must be patient.
cards.backText: Joskus täytyy jonottaa, mutta täytyy olla kärsivällinen.

cards.frontText: I have a doctor's certificate for my illness.
(noun) Sick leave (paid absence from work to recover from illness)
(It) is good to inform also when the sick leave will end.
cards.backText: On hyvä ilmoittaa myös, milloin sairausloma loppuu.

cards.frontText: (noun) Guardian (a person legally responsible for a minor). Custodian.
(noun) Date, a point in time (time + a point/moment)
I will tell you (plural) about the trip.
to turn (of age); to fill, to fill up, to fill in
Inkeri turns 30  years this summer. (puhekielinen numero)
I turn 25 years in the spring. (puhekielinen numero)
Inkeri's friends want to organise a surprise party for Inkeri.
cards.backText: Inkerin ystävät haluavat järjestää Inkerille yllätysjuhlat.

cards.frontText: I'm organizing a party on the weekend.
She is organizing a trip to Lapland with her family.
cards.backText: Hän järjestää matkan Lappiin perheensä kanssa.

cards.frontText: Can your coffee shop be rented for private events?
Yes. (can also used as an intensifier similar to English "do")
to succeed, to manage, to achieve a desired result
Yes it succeeds. (Yes, it can be done)
Even though the test is difficult, I succeed in it. (I can do it)
cards.backText: Vaikka testi on vaikea, minä onnistun siinä.

cards.frontText: Just a moment, I will check.
to order, to sign up for, to subscribe to
Do you (plural) also order foods from here?
I order two tickets to the movie for us.
cards.backText: Minä tilaan meille kaksi lippua elokuvaan.

cards.frontText: He rarely orders food from a restaurant, typically makes food at home.
cards.backText: Hän tilaa harvoin ruokaa ravintolasta, yleensä tekee ruokaa kotona.

cards.frontText: to think over, to ponder (think about sth carefully) (____ + Partitive)
She wonders, is this the right path (road).
cards.backText: Hän miettii, onko tämä oikea tie.

cards.frontText: Contact details, contact information (usually in plural form)
Oskar and Tiina exchange contact details.
to promise, to vow (____ + Partitive: to do; ____ + Mille: to someone)
(I) promise you, that (I) will come to the party.
He promises to help me with the homework.
cards.backText: Hän lupaa auttaa minua läksyjen kanssa.

cards.frontText: You promise to write to me every week.
cards.backText: Sinä lupaat kirjoittaa minulle joka viikko.

cards.frontText: to bring (coming toward the speaker, opposite of viedä), to import
I bring my coat inside, because (it's) raining outside .
cards.backText: Minä tuon takkini sisälle, koska ulkona sataa.

cards.frontText: He brings too much wood to the cottage.
Oskar promises that Inkeri's friends are allowed to bring their own foods.
cards.backText: Oskar lupaa, että Inkerin ystävät saavat tuoda omia ruokia.

cards.frontText: (adj) agreed, appointed (this word related to the verb to fit, to agree)
When everything is agreed, (we) can start the program.
cards.backText: Kun kaikki on sovittu, voimme aloittaa ohjelman.

cards.frontText: I'm planning a trip to Europe.
Tiina plans the invitation and sends it to all of Inkeri's friends.
cards.backText: Tiina suunnittelee kutsun ja lähettää sen kaikille Inkerin ystäville.

cards.frontText: to participate in, to take part in (____ + Mihin)
He takes part in all the exercises.
to hold a speech (to give/delivery a speech) (more formal than puhua)
I will give a long speech at work.
She gives a speech in front of the whole school.
cards.backText: Hän pitää puheen koko koulun edessä.

cards.frontText: (postp.) By, not later than (related to deadline or limit) (Mihin + ____)
What special (thing) do you know about the party?
to sound, to ring (object making sound by itself)
cards.etymology: related to verb: to play (music), to call

cards.frontText: What song is playing on the radio?
That's why I go to the café, because its owner is Oskar.
cards.backText: Siksi menen kahvilaan, koska sen omistaja on Oskar.

cards.frontText: to familiar with, to know (personal); to feel (actively)
I know her (by name), but I don't know her (personally).
cards.backText: Minä tiedän hänet, mutta minä en tunne häntä.

cards.frontText: Even though she knows a lot of people, she often eats alone.
cards.backText: Vaikka hän tuntee paljon ihmisiä, hän syö usein yksin.

cards.frontText: Do you, however, want to contribute (participate) to the gift (puhekieli)
to suggest, to propose (a plan, a solution) (offering a condition)
(I) suggest that (we) go to the cinema.
My shoes rub. He suggests that (I) buy new shoes. (puhekieli)
cards.backText: Mun kengät hankaa. Se ehdottaa, että ostan uudet kengät.

cards.frontText: Ingredient, material (similar to Aine, but often refer to an ingredient)
Yeast (used in baking - leivonnassa - or brewing)
Cardamom bread. Sweet roll, sweet bun.

cards.etymology: from verb: kastaa + KE (to dip in liquid)

cards.frontText: (noun) occasion (special event or function); opportunity, chance
His birthday is a special occasion to celebrate.
cards.backText: Hänen syntymäpäivänsä on erityinen tilaisuus juhlia.

cards.frontText: to move, to relocate (residence); to modify, to transform
A person (not specific) moves to a new home.
(I) will die of hunger (I will starve to death)
After the housewarming, (we) clean the apartment together. (puhekieli)
They arrive in the forest after a long journey.
cards.backText: He saapuvat metsään pitkän matkan jälkeen.

cards.frontText: to know how, to have skill to do something (different than voida)
Do you know how to speak Finnish?
She know how to drive a car.
He doesn't know how to swim.
to be allowed to ( + infinitive verb); to get, to receive
Must not disturb! Do not disturb!
Emma is not allowed to dance on the table.
The baby is not allowed to watch television.
You are not allowed to be late.
You are allowed to listen to music, but not too loud.
cards.backText: Sinä saat kuunnella musiikkia, mutta ei liian kovaa.

cards.frontText: (I) am allowed to go to the cinema, if (I) do homework first.
cards.backText: Saan mennä elokuviin, jos teen läksyt ensin.

cards.frontText: She is allowed to choose the lunch spot today.

cards.etymology: This the origin of two words: interesting; gladly

cards.frontText: (adv) gladly, with one's pleasure/mind (inflected by whose mind)
(I) wash gladly (with my pleasure) the floors after the party.
She visits gladly (with her pleasure) in a big city every summer.
cards.backText: Hän käy mielellään suuressa kaupungissa joka kesä.

cards.frontText: You take gladly (with your pleasure) company along on a trip.
cards.backText: Sinä otat mielelläsi seuraa mukaan matkalle.

cards.etymology: can be done by us (voidaan) = we can do (voimme)
it will be met (tavataan)= we will meet (tapaamme)

cards.frontText: We will meet there! See you there!
Can we meet somewhere before that party (in plural)? (puhekieli)
cards.backText: Voidaanko me tavata jossain ennen niitä juhlia?

cards.frontText: to fear, be afraid of (___ + Partitive)
cards.etymology: (refers to the feelings of the person who is afraid)

cards.frontText: He is afraid of the thunder.
I run today, eventhough it's snowing.
cards.backText: Minä juoksen tänään, vaikka sataa lunta.

cards.frontText: She runs every day to work.
I jump high when (I) am happy.
cards.backText: Minä hyppään korkealle, kun olen iloinen.

cards.frontText: He often jumps into the lake in summer.
I rarely argue with my coworkers.
He often argues with his friend.
I kiss my daughter on (her) head.
She kisses the man before leaving for work.
cards.backText: Hän suutelee miestä ennen töihin lähtöä.

cards.frontText: He is angry, because I'm lying to him.
cards.backText: Hän on vihainen, koska valehtelen hänelle.

cards.frontText: She is trustworthy and rarely lies.
cards.backText: Hän on luotettava ja valehtelee harvoin.

cards.frontText: (noun) a running, walking or skiing exercise. Chain link
He asks Inkeri out for a walk.
I congratulate you (plural) on your new home.
She congratulates them on wedding day.
to wonder at, to be puzzled, to ask in surprise (____ + Partitive)
I wonder why the cat is afraid of water.
cards.backText: Minä ihmettelen, miksi kissa pelkää vettä.

cards.frontText: Inkeri surprises (is surprised) when friends congratulate her.
cards.backText: Inkeri ihmettelee, kun ystävät onnittelevat häntä.

cards.frontText: From Inkeri (Inkeri finds) it is pleasant to be in good friends's company.
cards.backText: Inkeristä on mukavaa olla hyvien ystävien seurassa.

cards.frontText: I recall my old friends often.
(It) is nice to chat and reminisce old times.
cards.backText: On kivaa jutella ja muistella vanhoja aikoja.

cards.frontText: I notice that he is sad.
cards.backText: Minä huomaan, että hän on surullinen.

cards.frontText: She notices the dog in the yard.
Clean, pure (in the sense of being free from dirt or contaminants)
Behind those trees is a small lake. (puhekieli)
cards.backText: Noiden puiden takana on pieni järvi.

cards.frontText: (noun) Dessert (a sweet dish after at the end of a meal)
Can one get it without pineapple? (Is it possible to get …?)

cards.etymology: = ensi (ensi is for abstract: time, event)

cards.frontText: (I) I will get off the bus at the next stop.
I am thinking (wondering) what (I) do next.
(adj) next (relative to the present moment, refer to time or events)
I will participate in the course next week.
I'm moving to a new apartment next month.
cards.backText: Minä muutan uuteen asuntoon ensi kuussa.

cards.frontText: I shout to my friend (who) on the other side of the street.
cards.backText: Minä huudan ystävälleni kadun toisella puolella.

cards.frontText: He shouts when (he) is afraid of thunder.
(idiom) to feel like,  to would like, to fancy
In the hot summer, I feel like (have a craving for) ice cream.
cards.backText: Kuumana kesänä minun tekee mieli jäätelöä.

cards.frontText: You feel like going home early. (leaving for home)
cards.backText: Sinun tekee mieli lähteä kotiin aikaisin.

cards.frontText: On a dull evening (you) can, for example, read a book or listen to music.
cards.backText: Tylsänä iltana voit vaikka lukea kirjaa tai kuunnella musiikkia.

cards.frontText: to loathe, to detest (strongly dislike or hate) (____ + Partitive)
(not) anybody, (not) anyone, nobody (mostly used in negative)
No one can do it alone.
cards.backText: Ei kukaan voi tehdä sitä yksin

cards.frontText: (postp.) until (time); up to,  all the way to (space) (Mihin/Mille + ____)
The course continues until the end of February.
I travel by train from Helsinki up to Tampere.
He will come along to the trip.
We will come along even though we have a lot of work.
cards.backText: Me tulemme mukaan, vaikka meillä on paljon töitä.
